Dynamic Price is the best ex of net price. The scenario will be evaluated for eligibility, then the remainder of the investors will be evaluated for the net best ex. This depends on how a product is configured in Polly. Dynamic pricing adjustments (LLPAs, SRP, etc.) are used to calculate a client base rate from an investor base rate. While they are being included in the price calculation, dynamic pricing fields are not included in the pricing scenario API call as dynamic pricing is at a rate level than at the product level, hence increasing the payload size exponentially.
